ity function is slightly higher than that of the\nCfA sample. The integrated space density of Seyfert 2s is about 2 times that of\nSeyfert 1s over their common range in luminosity. In terms of the standard\nunified model, this ratio in space density corresponds to a typical half-angle\nof the torus of about 48 degress.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 28 Jun 1996 21:39:55 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-10-28"}
